			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>So if no-one is going to make Teachers TV programmes anymore in the future &#8211; why don&#8217;t we do it ourselves?</p>
<p>For a few years now I have been perfecting how to do this with minimal equipment and maximising the use of web based services &#8211; I think I would be able to run a Teachers TV equivalent on a shoestring and get people to upload their own content.</p>
<p>I think this should be a ground up initiative and involve schools at source and Social Enterprise services</p>
<p>Obviously people will have to think of IPR and copyright and privacy considerations but the few people who&#8217;d like to take this forwards &#8211; especially Schools, FE, HE and ITT institutions and organisations like the TDA &#8211;  I&#8217;d be very interested in working with you.</p>
<p>What do people think?</p>
<p>Let me know&#8230;</p>
<p>See the video below.</p>
