		<description><![CDATA[Well what a week it has been! Since receiving a letter on the 21st April about the closure of Teachers TV on 29th April and then proposing on twitter via the hashtag #saveTTV, that everyone should do exactly that: &#8220;save&#8221; Teachers TV, there have been so many wonderful things happen. The next day I put [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="alignnone" src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5183/5665815641_94a5cd85c1_b.jpg" alt="" width="512" height="388" /></p>
<p>Well what a week it has been!</p>
<p>Since receiving a letter on the 21st April about the closure of Teachers TV on <strong>29th April</strong> and then proposing on twitter via the hashtag #saveTTV, that everyone should do exactly that: &#8220;save&#8221; Teachers TV, there have been so many wonderful things happen.</p>
<p>The next day I put up a Google Docs Spreadsheet for people to log their downloads and a small band of people got together the very next day and sat down to save all the Teachers TV videos.</p>
<p>I had suggested that they all be cached on a Dropbox and asked for funding:</p>
<p>Dawn Hallybone, Gideon Williams, Anne Fielder, Jackie Berry, DrBob (Teacher -West London), Robert Rollins, Jen Kenny, Sinclair Mackenzie, Stuart Swann, Colin Revell, Carol Rainbow, Heather Marshall, Alexander Bellars Theo Kuechel, Penny Patterson (twice!!), Dale Jones, John Heffernan, Alan Stewart and Ceri Williams all responded immediately and we had space for caching.</p>
<p>Four days later, thanks to the efforts of everyone below, everything has been saved.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.twitter.com/ianaddison" target="_blank">@ianaddison</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/penny_patterson" target="_blank">@penny_patterson</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/bobtoms100" target="_blank">@bobtoms100</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/carolrainbow" target="_blank">@carolrainbow</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/lisibo" target="_blank">@lisibo</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/nickynewbury" target="_blank">@nickynewbury</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/ebd35" target="_blank">@ebd35</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/dan_bowen" target="_blank">@dan_bowen</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/moodledan" target="_blank">@moodledan</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/mattlovegrove" target="_blank">@mattlovegrove</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/mrmackenzie" target="_blank">@mrmackenzie</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/#!/johnjohnston" target="_blank">@johnjohnston</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/bellaale" target="_blank">@bellaale</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/russdev" target="_blank">@russdev</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/billgibbon" target="_blank">@billgibbon</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/stevebunce" target="_blank">@stevebunce</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/TWMarkChambers" target="_blank">@TWMarkChambers</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/bevevans22" target="_blank">@bevevans22</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/cypherite" target="_blank">@cypherite</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/cerirwilliams" target="_blank">@cerirwilliams</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/bobweb2" target="_blank">@bobweb2</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/ciaje74" target="_blank">@ciaje74</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/dannynic" target="_blank">@dannynic</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/wlonline" target="_blank">@wlonline</a>, <a href="http://twitter.com/stuartswann" target="_blank">@stuartswann</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/frogphilp" target="_blank">@frogphilp</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/theokk" target="_blank">@theokk</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/ClaireJoanne35" target="_blank">@ClaireJoanne35</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/AmandaWilson169" target="_blank">@AmandaWilson169</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/richardmillwood" target="_blank">@richardmillwood</a>, <a href="http://www.twitter.com/grumbledook" target="_blank">@grumbledook</a></p>
<p>If I have missed anyone out please accept my apologies.</p>
<p>During the last couple of hours before the site was due to go down, the TES and other major players said they had expressed an interest to the DfE about getting a licence to &#8220;stream&#8221; the entire video catalogue.</p>
<p>But all the archive has already been saved by teachers to their drives for use in UK schools under the Creative Archive licence.</p>
<p>Towards the end of the process even Andrew Bethell, the <span>ex CEO and Director of External Affairs at Teachers TV, said: </span></p>
<p>&#8220;<em>Great work. this is an amazing affirmation of what we achieved  a real benefit to our users. Thanks.</em>&#8221;</p>
<p><strong>What Next?</strong></p>
<p>Well &#8211; we now have a central list of people in possession of the video files. The DropBox will be used, not to distribute, but to cache the files for transfer to media to be used in UK schools and educational institutions.</p>
<p>In the meantime if you want something specific &#8211; ask one of the teachers on the <a href="https://spreadsheets.google.com/ccc?key=0AqOhBi9yGR1LdFhtNDhIejRNSGpxQUNvV3FfcXdGNFE&amp;hl=en_GB#gid=0" target="_blank">Google Doc spreadsheet list</a> of the series of files and I&#8217;m sure they will be of help.</p>
<p>At the time of writing the DfE has now repositioned its response by saying the files will all be back up in a couple of weeks&#8217; time but I suspect it may take longer than that. My question is, why weren&#8217;t they up straight after the site is being shut down? Anyway, we have yet to see&#8230;</p>
<p>#saveTTV was never intended to be a distribution system, merely an interim measure, but everyone is well aware teachers prefer to have the physical files &#8220;in-house&#8221; because you try giving CPD to colleagues or a lesson starter to a group of Year 9&#8242;s on a wet Wednesday afternoon. The #saveTTV initiative is intended to complement any streaming service that will emerge in the future.</p>
<p>What we need now, is a weekly CPD Teachers TV station on YouTube. Anyone up for that?</p>
<p>Thank you again everyone. I will be in touch &#8211; give me a week to let the dust settle please. Get in touch by email in the meantime.</p>
<p>Best Wishes and enjoy the holiday!</p>
<p>Leon  Cych</p>
